The paper deals with the task of figure extraction in scientific documents using deep neural networks. This task involves image processing and natural language processing, which are common themes in several sub-categories of computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on scientific documents, it is likely that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks for figure extraction suggests that the paper could also belong to the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category. The paper also involves image processing, which is a key theme in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of large datasets and data-driven methods suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
